# Node.js Environment

- System Node.js version: **v25** (NODE_MODULE_VERSION 141)
- Electron ships its own Node (currently v22 / MODULE_VERSION 133)
- Native modules (e.g. `better-sqlite3`) must be compiled for Electron's Node, not the system Node
- Use `npx electron-builder install-app-deps` (the `postinstall` script) to rebuild native modules for Electron — never use bare `npm rebuild` as it targets the system Node and breaks the Electron app
- After any `npm install` or native dependency change, verify with `npm run preview` that the app still launches
